---
import ArticleContainer from "../../components/ArticleContainer.astro";
import PageLayout from "../../layouts/PageLayout.astro";
---

<PageLayout title="CapyNow Privacy Policy">
  <ArticleContainer>
    <article>
      <h1>CapyNow Privacy Policy</h1>

      <p><strong>Effective Date:</strong> 12/17/23</p>

      <p>Thank you for choosing CapyNow! This Privacy Policy explains how we handle your information when you
        use our iOS application. Please take a moment to read through this document to understand our practices
        regarding your privacy.</p>

      <h2>1. Information We Do Not Collect:</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>We do not collect any personally identifiable information (PII) from users of CapyNow.</li>
        <li>We do not access, store, or process any personal data, including but not limited to names, email addresses,
          phone numbers, or any other sensitive information.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>2. Device Permissions:</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>CapyNow requests access to your device's location services for the CapyMap feature.</li>
        <li>Location data is used solely within the app and is neither stored by us nor transmitted to our servers.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>3. Analytics and Tracking:</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>We do not use any third-party analytics tools or services to track user behavior within the app.</li>
        <li>No data about your usage patterns, interactions, or preferences is collected or analyzed.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>4. Advertising:</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>CapyNow does not display third-party advertisements.</li>
        <li>We do not use any advertising networks or collect any data for ad targeting purposes.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>5. Communication:</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>CapyNow does not send any promotional emails, notifications, or communications to users.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>6. Updates and Improvements:</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>We may periodically release updates to improve the functionality and user experience of CapyNow.</li>
        <li>These updates will be delivered through the Apple App Store and will not involve the collection of
          additional user data.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>7. Children's Privacy:</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>CapyNow is suitable for users of all ages, including children under the age of 13.</li>
        <li>We do not knowingly collect personal information from children.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>8. Security:</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>We employ industry-standard security measures to protect any non-personal information that may be collected
          incidentally, such as crash logs, from unauthorized access.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>9. Changes to this Privacy Policy:</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Any updates to this Privacy Policy will be reflected in the app's App Store listing. Please review the
          policy periodically for changes.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>10. Contact Us:</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>If you have any questions, concerns, or requests regarding your privacy and CapyNow, please contact
          us at max@mmaeder.com.</li>
      </ul>

      <p>By using CapyNow, you signify your consent to this Privacy Policy. If you do not agree with the terms of
        this policy, please do not use the app.</p>

      <p>Thank you for trusting CapyNow with your privacy.</p>
    </article>
  </ArticleContainer>
</PageLayout>

<style>
  article {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    overflow-x: hidden;
  }
  h2 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
  }
</style>